title: The Fruit of the Tree
creator: Edith Wharton
description: LibriVox recording of The Fruit of the Tree, by Edith Wharton. Read by Margaret Espaillat. When published in 1907, this novel about the lives of a wealthy mill owner, her socially progressive husband and friends caused a stir due to its treatment of drug abuse, mercy killing, divorce and second marriages. reviews.reviewbody: Wharton is a great writer, but in this novel she over psychoanalyzes far too much, here in The Fruit of the Tree. Perhaps characters of the upper classes have complex and convoluted psychological make up, but I don't think the rest of us have the time to invent so many psychological weapons to exploit each other with.  look to we the people for a more equitable and life worth living.
